From Mitch Kapor Subject Re Jerry Berman on pseudonymous privacy correctly states Jerry Berman's view on privacy but he mistakenly assumes that this represents Berman's view as EFF Executive As one of the people who convinced Jerry that legal protections for privacy are insufficient and that technical measures especially public key cryptography are also vitally necessary I can tell you that Jerry and EFF are fully committed to this The previous poster is apparently unaware of a long series of EFF positions in support of this I suggest those interested read EFF's position on Clipper or our other work in digital Check for more One of the great things about human beings is that they are capable of change and evolution in their The idea that crypto is critical to privacy is one which is no longer limited to certain net afficianados but is spreading to parts of the public policy community in Mitch Kapor co Founder EFF